Each year, the Learn Fresh staff nominates educators from across the country, who have gone above and beyond for their students in our programs. To conclude Teacher Appreciation Week, join us in celebrating these All-Star Educators.
•
•
While we are only able to recognize this small group, we know every educator across the country is working diligently to support their students during these difficult times. THANK YOU for your dedication, passion and support of young learners! While we are grateful for you all year long, now more than ever, we recognize the profound impact you have on so many young lives. #teacherappreciationweek #allstar #education #teacher

Just go to www.2020Census.org

⭐️ THIS WEEKS LIVE STREAMS AND EDUCATIONAL VIDEOS SCHEDULE! ⭐️

Commencing on Monday 30th March, tune in for a week of both fun and exciting action this week as we kick off our first live streams and educational videos! Here's when to catch the action! 👇🐨🦘

The educational videos at 10am will be posted on Tim Faulkner’s Facebook and Instagram pages as well as the Australian Reptile Park’s YouTube channel 🐍🐢

post_text:
Dear Parents and Guardians,

On Monday morning, February 10th at approximately 7:45 AM, a Crocker student was walking in the area of Chateau and Ralston when a man slowly approached him in his car. The man asked the student if he wanted a ride. The student said no. We were just made aware of this information today (2/12) and immediately called the Hillsborough Police Department (HPD) who came to Crocker Middle School to speak with the student and his parent.

Your child’s safety is of utmost importance to us. Parents are asked to remind their children about the importance of avoiding strangers and reporting any incident of contact by strangers to their teacher or principal.

As educators, we strongly encourage parents to talk to your children about stranger awareness. Please click on this link: http://archive.ncpc.org/topics/violent-crime-and-personal-safety/strangers.html for helpful talking points from the National Crime Prevention Council.

Thank you,
Louann Carlomagno
Superintendent
shared_text:
Hillsborough Police Department
February 12 at 1:37 PM ·

The Hillsborough Police Department is investigating a report of a suspicious person and vehicle near Crocker School that was reported today (02-12-2020). The incident occurred on 02-10-2020 between 7:45AM and 8:00AM. A student who was walking to school was approached by a gray or silver 4-Door newer sedan, and the driver asked the student if he needed a ride to school. The student refused the ride and the driver left without further incident. The student described the driver as a white male adult, approximately 60 years old, with gray and white hair, clean-shaven, and was wearing sunglasses. The driver was wearing a white shirt with buttons, a red tie, and dark colored slacks.

If you have any information that would assist us in identifying the suspicious person, or vehicle, please call our Communications Center at 650-375-7470.

Press Information Contact:

Captain Nelson Corteway
1-650-375-7552 (Office)
ncorteway@hillsborough.net

shared_text:
Associated Parents' Groups of Hillsborough
November 9, 2019 at 4:40 PM ·

Walk & Roll, Hillsborough!
Our first district-wide walk/bike to school day is coming up this Friday, Nov. 15. We are encouraging all HCSD students to walk or ride their bikes to and from school on Friday. We hope that this (and future monthly dates) will help raise awareness around safe routes to school, encourage healthy habits, reduce our carbon footprint, and foster a community that prioritizes our students getting to school safely!

Hillsborough Police Department has kindly offered to support this effort by monitoring school intersections and providing a bike meet-up area for North School participants at the Walnut Lot across the street from Town Hall starting around 8am.

Drivers: Please be extra vigilant on November 15th in the morning and afternoon as there will be more foot and bicycle traffic than usual.

post_text:
FUN RUN RACE PORTION CANCELLED!! We are sorry to report that due to the risk of thunderstorms, we are CANCELLING the Hillsborough Fun Run race portion ONLY. We did not make this decision lightly and do believe it is in the best interests of participants and everyone involved to stay off the course given the current weather conditions. We would love for you to join us for breakfast at the North MPR, where you can also pick up your race t-shirt until 10:00am. If you can't pick up your race t-shirt today, please stop by the HSF office at 300 El Cerrito Avenue, Hillsborough Monday to Friday between 9:00am-4:30pm. We sincerely apologize for any inconvenience.

Hillsborough Schools Foundation
300 El Cerrito Ave, Hillsborough, CA 94010
(650) 344-6685
